1. To craete Shell variables (Shell variables means only accessible within the shell script)
  TEST_VAR='Hello World!'
  
2. To make shell vraibles as Environemnet variables (Environment Variables are accesible to child process)
  export TEST_VAR
  
3. To create new Environment variables (Once the shell is closed the environment variables are destroyed. And the child process environment variables cannot
be accessed by parent)
  export NEW_VAR="Testing export"
  
4. To see the environment variables
  printenv
  printenv variable_name (To print the environment variable value)

5. To list all shell variables, environmental variables, local variables, and shell functions
  set
  
6. To change Environment variable to shell variable
  export -n TEST_VAR
  
7. If we want to completely unset a variable, either shell or environmental
  unset TEST_VAR
  
8. 
